MONTCLAIR, N.J., Oct. 31, — Mrs. Joan Drukker Benner, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Dow H. Drukker Jr. of Upper Mont­clair, was married this after­noon to Councilman Arthur J. Sullivan Jr. of Clifton, son of Mrs. Sullivan of Passaic and the late Mr. Sullivan, who was Park Commissioner of Passaic County.

The Rev. Raymond Pontier of the Allwood Community Church (Reformed) in Clifton performed the ceremony at the home of the bride's parents. He was assisted by the Rev. Rich­ard N. Bolles, rector of St. John's Episcopal Church in Passaic.

Mrs. Charles Spicer, sister of the bridegroom, and Charles Shaw attended the couple.

The bride is a graduate of the Emma Willard School in Troy, N.Y., and Smith College. Her father is a former Commissioner of the Port of New York Au­thority and her grandfather, the late Dow H. Drulcker, was a United States Representative from New Jersey. The bride's previous marriage ended in di­vorce.

